At 04:09 PM 2/24/2004 -0500, Billy wrote:
>Doesn't WD-40 have components that evaporate quickly?
>Kerosene or some such?

Bingo!  Check out the brain on Billy!

WD-40 is kerosene--with perfumes added, so you think you're squirting
something besides plain-old kerosene into your stuck gizmos.

Kroil makes a much better unsticker, and motor oil, STP Oil Treatment,
Bosch Distributor Grease, brake lube, and moly greases make better lubricants.

